Citizens Financial Group, Inc. Key Developments

Citizens Commercial Banking Hires Laura Neenan Fogarty as Head of Healthcare Banking
Jul 25 17
Citizens Bank has announced that Citizens Commercial Banking has hired Laura Neenan Fogarty as head of its national healthcare banking group. Fogarty joins Citizens following a successful 20-year banking career providing solutions to corporate clients, most recently serving as Managing Director of Healthcare Corporate Banking at Citigroup. Prior to joining Citigroup, Fogarty worked as a corporate banker at the Bank of New York and Bank of America.


Citizens Commercial Banking Appoints Laura Neenan Fogarty as Head of National Healthcare Banking Group
Jul 24 17
Citizens Bank announced that Citizens Commercial Banking has hired Laura Neenan Fogarty as head of its national healthcare banking group. Fogarty joins Citizens following a successful 20-year banking career providing solutions to corporate clients, most recently serving as Managing Director of Healthcare Corporate Banking at Citigroup. Prior to joining Citigroup, Fogarty worked as a corporate banker at the Bank of New York and Bank of America.


Citizens Financial Group, Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017; Reports Net Charge-Offs or the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 21 17
Citizens Financial Group, Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net interest income of $1,026 million compared to $923 million a year ago. Total revenue was $1,396 million compared to $1,278 million a year ago. Net income was $318 million compared to $243 million a year ago. Net income available to common stockholders was $318 million or $0.63 per diluted share compared to $243 million or $0.46 per diluted share a year ago. Return on average common equity was 6.5% compared to 4.9% a year ago. Return on average tangible common equity was 9.6% compared to 7.3% a year ago. Return on average total assets was 0.85% compared to 0.69% a year ago. Return on average total tangible assets was 0.89% compared to 0.72% a year ago. Underlying net interest income was $1,026 million. Underlying total revenue was $1,407 million. Underlying net income was $318 million or $0.63 per diluted share. Non-GAAP total revenue, adjusted was $1,396 million compared to $1,278 million a year ago. Non-GAAP income before income tax expense, adjusted was $462 million compared to $361 million a year ago. Non-GAAP net income, adjusted was $318 million compared to $243 million a year ago. Non-GAAP net income available to common stockholders, adjusted was $318 million or $0.63 per basic and diluted share compared to $243 million or $0.46 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average common equity, adjusted was 6.48% compared to 4.94% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average tangible common equity, adjusted was 9.57% compared to 7.30% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average total assets, adjusted was 0.85% compared to 0.69% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average total tangible assets, adjusted was 0.89% compared to 0.72% a year ago. Non-GAAP total revenue, underlying was $1,407 million compared to $1,278 million a year ago. Non-GAAP net income, underlying was $318 million compared to $21 million a year ago. Non-GAAP net income available to common stockholders, underlying was $318 million or $0.63 per basic and diluted share compared to $28 million or $0.46 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average common equity, underlying was 6.48% compared to 4.94% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average tangible common equity, underlying was 9.57% compared to 7.30% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average total assets, underlying was 0.85% compared to 0.69% a year ago. Non-GAAP return on average total tangible assets, underlying was 0.89% compared to 0.72% a year ago. Tangible book value per common share was $26.61 compared to $25.72 a year ago.

For the second quarter ended June 30, 2017, the company's net charge-offs were $75 million against $65 million a year ago.


